The paper discusses a learning and reasoning system for automated theorem proving, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The system also deals with large formal libraries and uses machine learning techniques, which are relevant to the sub-categories of logic in computer science (cs.LO) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also mentions the use of natural language processing (NLP) techniques, which is relevant to the sub-category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). Finally, the paper discusses the evaluation of the system, which is relevant to the sub-category of cryptography and security (cs.CR).
